Dec 4 (Reuters) - Bitcoin dived 12.14% to $47,176.09 on Saturday, losing $6,567.6 from its previous close. Bitcoin, the world's biggest and best-known cryptocurrency, is down 31.6% from the year's high of $69,000 reached on Nov. 10. Ether , the coin linked to the ethereum blockchain network, dropped 10.14 % to $3,794.61 on Saturday, losing $428.19 from its previous close. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.